{"lemma":"أَشْقِياءُ","slug":"أَشْقِياءُ","root":"ش.ق.#","root_slug":"ش-ق-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ق-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"شَقِيّ","root":"شقو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":4},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22711","n22773","n22777","n22781"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B4%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%A1%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be unhappy, to be miserable","examples":[{"text":"فَقُلْنَا يَا آدَمُ إِنَّ هَٰذَا عَدُوٌّ لَّكَ وَلِزَوْجِكَ فَلَا يُخْرِجَنَّكُمَا مِنَ الْجَنَّةِ فَتَشْقَىٰ"},{"text":"ذُو الْعَقْلِ يَشْقَى فِي النَّعِيمِ بِعَقْلِهِ\nوَأَخُو الْجَهَالَةِ فِي الشَّقَاوَةِ يَنْعَمُ\nḏū l-ʕaqli yašqā fī n-naʕīmi biʕaqlihi","english":"(please add an English translation of this quotation)"}]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"unhappy, miserable","examples":[{"text":"يَوْمَ يَأْتِ لَا تَكَلَّمُ نَفْسٌ إِلَّا بِإِذْنِهِ ۚ فَمِنْهُمْ شَقِيٌّ وَسَعِيدٌ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʃa.qijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22711","headword_ar":"شَقِّىٌّ","root":"$q","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which his rider ex-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1579},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"periences difficulty in striving to master him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n22773","headword_ar":"شَقِىَ","root":"$qw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiwa","text_ar":"شَقِوَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) dual thereof"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$oqayaAni","text_ar":"يَشْقَيَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAwapN","text_ar":"شَقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqaAwapN","text_ar":"شِقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, * K,) the latter accord. to a reading of the Kur xxiii. 108, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaA='N","text_ar":"شَقَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqowapN","text_ar":"شِقْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqowapN","text_ar":"شَقْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqFA","text_ar":"شَقًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K.) or the last of these is the inf. n., and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAwapN","text_ar":"شَقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$iqowapN","text_ar":"شِقْوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and the rest, none of which is expressly specified as an inf. n. in the S,] are simple substs., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1582},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, unprosperous, unfortunate, unhappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"miserable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqiYa","text_ar":"شَقِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEida","text_ar":"سَعِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAwapN","text_ar":"شَقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaAdapN","text_ar":"سَعَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, in a state of straitness, distress, adversity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAwapN","text_ar":"شَقَاوَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He suffered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"experienced, fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, and Ksh and Bd and Jel in xx. 1,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY ka*aA","text_ar":"فِى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in such a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaAhu","text_ar":"شَقَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3: ―         -b2-  and 4."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22777","headword_ar":"شَقِىٌّ","root":"$qw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Unprosperous, unfortunate, unhappy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"miserable:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, TA:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in a state of straitness, distress, adversity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"difficulty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see its verb:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oqiyaA='u","text_ar":"اَشْقِيَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"walamN A^akuno biduEaAy^ika rab~i $aqiy~FA","text_ar":"وَلَمٌ اَكُنْ بِدُعَايِكَ رَبِّ شَقِيًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xix. 4,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I have not been, in supplicating Thee, my Lord, unprosperous"},{"kind":"text","text":"], means I have been one whose prayer has been answered. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n22781","headword_ar":"شَقَى","root":"$qY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqoYN","text_ar":"شَقْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAb","text_ar":"نَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or tush] of a camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It grew forth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaA^a","text_ar":"شَقَاَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$qw","text_ar":"شقو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but belonging to the present art.: mentioned in the TA, as not in the K, on the authority of ISd].) ―         -b2-  [Freytag states, as on the authority of Abu-l-'Alà, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aqaY","text_ar":"شَقَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aq~a","text_ar":"شَقَّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He clave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"split,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: ―         -b3-  and that Reiske has explained it as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He opened the mouth with a wide grinning"},{"kind":"text","text":"(“ amplo rictu ” ).]"}],"source_refs":[]}]}}